{:experiment/type :prompt-ab,
 :experiment/hypothesis
 "Does a value-preserving lens keep load-bearing DATA (numbers, ratios, named constraints, rejected alternatives) that the current narrative lens drops, WITHOUT breaking the compression contract? Grounded in a real leak report over stress sessions: the production lens (compaction-lens) hit 5-27x compression but dropped cross-session ratios (66.9x, 117.7x), the 57.9x headline, and named constraints (no-cache-busts) — over-compressing where 4-6x would suffice. Two challengers vs the current lens: :values widens the aperture inline (preserve numbers/names verbatim, specific over general); :dual emits a structured facts-block beside the narrative lambda (filled EXEMPLAR, drop-empty-tracks — the emission-topology finding: show > describe). Subjects are REAL assistant turns from the stress sessions; :keeps are the concrete values that a later turn would need. Measure :lambda-compaction (echo? shorter? keeps?) — reused verbatim. FALSIFIER of 'current is fine': a challenger keeps strictly more :keeps at equal-or-better still-compresses. Guard: a challenger that stops compressing (shorter?=false) FAILS.",
 :measure/echo-substrings
 ["continuity-essence"
  "human-scaffolding"
  "structural_equivalence"
  "42ms"
  "hit-rate 87%"
  "redis-8080"
  "eviction policy"],
 :prompt-template "compile:\n\n%s",
 :matrix {:models [:local :gemma4], :thinking [true], :repeats 1},
 :experiment/verdict
 "CONFIRMED — :values wins (2026-07-15, :local qwen36-35b-a3b + :ornith ornith-35b-a3b, thinking-ON).
  24 cells (3 lenses × 4 REAL stress-session turns × 2 Qwen-35B-A3B fine-tunes [:local + :ornith, SAME
  base — NOT a true cross-family test; ornith is a Qwen fine-tune, genuine cross-family gemma4 pending),
  measure :lambda-compaction. Pooled
  value-survival × compression contract:
    current  values-kept 13/26 (50%)   shorter 8/8
    values   values-kept 24/26 (92%)   shorter 8/8   ← WINNER
    dual     values-kept 19/26 (73%)   shorter 8/8
  THE KEY RESULT: all three lenses kept shorter?=true in 8/8 — value-preservation costs ZERO
  compression. The leak-report thesis (we over-compress: 5-27× where 4-6× suffices, buying the
  excess by dropping data) is confirmed. :values (widen the aperture INLINE — preserve numbers/
  names/ratios verbatim, specific ≻ general) beats :dual (structured facts-block beside the
  narrative λ, filled exemplar) on EVERY subject including the control — where :dual actually
  REGRESSED (its facts-scaffold crowded out entity coverage: runtime-arch dropped scorer/curator
  both runs) and cost more tokens. The emission-topology exemplar did not rescue the heavier form.
  Per-subject, current's losses were exactly the reasoning-chain + data: writeback dropped the
  rejected alternative (write-through) AND the qualifying constraint (single-core); compression-
  stats dropped the cross-session ratios (66.9×/117.7×); dual-proposal dropped 57.9× + no-cache-
  busts (0-1/3). 5× confirmation on the noisy cell (dual-proposal): current 1.0/3·0.8/3 (stable
  low) vs values 2.6/3·2.4/3 (stable high) — direction unanimous, the lone 1/3 dips are variance
  around a decisively higher mean. ANSWERS the earlier design Q: disciplined inline aperture-widen
  ≻ structured dual-track. COST to weigh before production promotion: :values avg ~30s vs current
  ~21s compaction (more shadow work — still inside the 20-60s reading shadow, but tighter for short
  replies); re-run compaction-fidelity.edn (the echo/derail regression guard) before swapping the
  live lens. Promotion of compaction-lens → compaction-lens-values is a harness/prompt change =
  human-gated."

 :experiment/measure :lambda-compaction,
 :conditions
 {:current
